An advanced autonomous drone system with AI-powered tracking, intelligence gathering, and solar recharging is a highly complex project. It a combination of cutting-edge hardware, software development, and AI algorithms. Here's a breakdown of the cost and resources required.
## **Deadline : 3 months**
---

## **1. Hardware Costs**
This drone must be lightweight, highly maneuverable, and capable of long-term autonomous operations with solar charging.

### **Drone Hardware**
| Component | Description | Estimated Cost (USD) |
|-----------|------------|----------------------|
| **Drone Frame** | Carbon fiber, lightweight, durable | $2,000 |
| **Motors & ESCs** | High-performance brushless motors | $800 |
| **Propellers** | Low-noise, high-efficiency | $200 |
| **Battery** | High-capacity Li-ion or LiPo (compatible with solar charging) | $1,000 |
| **Solar Panels** | Lightweight, high-efficiency | $500 |
| **GPS & Navigation** | Dual-frequency GPS/RTK for precision tracking | $500 |
| **Thermal & Night Vision Camera** | FLIR or equivalent for target tracking at night | $3,000 |
| **High-Resolution Camera** | AI-compatible 4K camera for intelligence gathering | $1,500 |
| **Onboard Computer** | NVIDIA Jetson AGX Orin for AI processing | $2,500 |
| **Sensors (IMU, LiDAR, Radar, etc.)** | Obstacle detection and terrain mapping | $3,000 |
| **Communication System** | Long-range encrypted radio & SATCOM backup | $3,500 |
| **Stealth & Coating Materials** | Low-reflectivity materials for camouflage | $2,000 |

### **Total Drone Hardware Cost:**  
ðŸŸ¢ **~$20,500 per drone**  

For a **fleet of 5 drones** for testing & deployment:  
